1
00:00:04,771 --> 00:00:06,940
This is Yuki Hamura
from the drama department.

2
00:00:07,474 --> 00:00:09,342
We joined the company in the same year.

3
00:00:09,409 --> 00:00:11,311
What's the matter? Did you have an affair?

4
00:00:11,378 --> 00:00:12,545
That's rude.

5
00:00:12,612 --> 00:00:15,515
Come on, who hasn't had an affair or two?

6
00:00:15,582 --> 00:00:17,951
Affairs were all the rage in Showa 60.

7
00:00:18,018 --> 00:00:19,853
Even Eiji Bando was popular.

8
00:00:19,919 --> 00:00:21,688
Haven't you heard of <i>Kintsuma</i>?

9
00:00:29,195 --> 00:00:31,297
D-Don't worry.

10
00:00:31,364 --> 00:00:33,967
In the end, he'll be really empathetic.

11
00:00:35,168 --> 00:00:38,171
Starting this spring, she's teaming up
with a big-shot scriptwriter

12
00:00:38,238 --> 00:00:39,839
to create a new drama.

13
00:00:39,906 --> 00:00:42,075
Have you heard of Kentaro Emo?

14
00:00:42,142 --> 00:00:44,411
The only screenwriter I know
is James Miki.

15
00:00:45,645 --> 00:00:47,981
From the late 90s to the early 2000s,

16
00:00:48,048 --> 00:00:51,151
he was the leading writer
who had massive support from the youth.

17
00:00:51,217 --> 00:00:53,186
He's famous for <i>An Eye for an Eye and</i>…

18
00:00:53,253 --> 00:00:54,521
<i>Love for My Brother</i>.

19
00:00:54,587 --> 00:00:57,657
Oh, yeah! Back in high school,
everyone was hooked on it.

20
00:00:57,724 --> 00:00:59,559
That iconic scene in the broadcast room.

21
00:00:59,626 --> 00:01:02,829
"I can't return your love, because I…"

22
00:01:03,463 --> 00:01:06,566
And then, Haruka, the protagonist,
realizes the mic is on.

23
00:01:06,633 --> 00:01:08,435
Exactly, she realizes the mic is on!

24
00:01:08,501 --> 00:01:10,703
Haruka freaks out
and pushes the teacher down.

25
00:01:11,271 --> 00:01:13,106
But then the teacher drops the bomb.

26
00:01:13,173 --> 00:01:15,775
"Because I'm your brother."

27
00:01:16,342 --> 00:01:18,812
And it's broadcast to the whole school!

28
00:01:18,878 --> 00:01:21,147
Every student in the school hears it.

29
00:01:21,214 --> 00:01:24,217
Then, in the gym,
someone shoots a basketball,

30
00:01:24,284 --> 00:01:26,519
and it shifts to slow motion,
but the ball…

31
00:01:26,586 --> 00:01:27,454
misses.

32
00:01:27,520 --> 00:01:30,323
It misses! That was a metaphor, wasn't it?

33
00:01:30,390 --> 00:01:31,958
He was the wizard of metaphors!

34
00:01:33,326 --> 00:01:34,861
You're not impressed?

35
00:01:36,062 --> 00:01:38,498
No. That's not true. I'm enjoying this.

36
00:01:39,132 --> 00:01:40,967
Oh, speaking of Emoken,

37
00:01:41,034 --> 00:01:43,136
there was a drama
about a street gang in Shimbashi?

38
00:01:43,203 --> 00:01:45,038
<i>SSLP</i>, <i>Shimbashi SL Park</i>.

39
00:01:45,105 --> 00:01:46,940
We used to copy the SL boys' fashion!

40
00:01:47,006 --> 00:01:49,576
What was the iconic line
from the protagonist again?

41
00:01:49,642 --> 00:01:50,944
"That's so neutral!"

42
00:01:51,010 --> 00:01:52,178
"So neutral!"

43
00:01:52,679 --> 00:01:54,347
Not many chances
to drop that line these days.

44
00:01:54,414 --> 00:01:55,515
I know, right?

45
00:01:57,283 --> 00:01:58,818
Sorry for leaving you hanging.

46
00:02:00,720 --> 00:02:02,522
No worries. Don't mind me.

47
00:02:03,623 --> 00:02:06,426
Anyway, he's like the
embodiment of my youth.

48
00:02:06,493 --> 00:02:08,995
I've always dreamt
of working with him in this industry,

49
00:02:09,062 --> 00:02:10,296
but it was impossible!

50
00:02:10,363 --> 00:02:12,532
I didn't want to risk
seeming like a cringy fan.

51
00:02:12,599 --> 00:02:14,501
So your dream finally came true.

52
00:02:15,135 --> 00:02:17,904
Yes. We had a meeting today.

53
00:02:17,971 --> 00:02:19,005
As it turns out…

54
00:02:21,341 --> 00:02:22,509
I wish I never met him.

55
00:02:23,910 --> 00:02:27,580
It's been so long since I've visited EBS.
What was my last project?

56
00:02:27,647 --> 00:02:30,150
<i>Love Navigation</i> in 2003.

57
00:02:30,216 --> 00:02:32,152
<i>LN</i>, huh?

58
00:02:32,218 --> 00:02:34,354
You guys probably don't know me.

59
00:02:34,420 --> 00:02:35,688
I bet you weren't even born.

60
00:02:37,924 --> 00:02:40,260
Anyway, it's an honor to collaborate with…

61
00:02:40,326 --> 00:02:42,662
I have a fun story
about the <i>LN</i> wrap-up party.

62
00:02:43,229 --> 00:02:46,766
We were at an Italian place in Roppongi,
and I had a little spat with Johnny.

63
00:02:46,833 --> 00:02:48,368
You know him as Giba now.

64
00:02:48,434 --> 00:02:50,336
And Show Aikawa ended up stopping us.

65
00:02:50,904 --> 00:02:53,106
As we were leaving,
the bill was already settled.

66
00:02:53,173 --> 00:02:54,340
Guess who covered it.

67
00:02:54,407 --> 00:02:56,509
-<i>What do you call it, idle talk?</i>
-Mariko Kaga.

68
00:02:56,576 --> 00:02:58,711
<i>He kept on bragging for nearly two hours.</i>

69
00:02:59,279 --> 00:03:00,246
And it was all…

70
00:03:00,313 --> 00:03:02,215
-Is it behind the times?
-Exactly.

71
00:03:02,282 --> 00:03:05,818
He was totally dwelling on the past
in his choice of words and topics.

72
00:03:05,885 --> 00:03:10,156
What inspired me to join this industry
was your <i>Eye for an Eye and</i>…

73
00:03:10,223 --> 00:03:12,325
I can't stand people
who dwell on the past.

74
00:03:14,227 --> 00:03:15,862
Right. I'm sorry.

75
00:03:15,929 --> 00:03:17,730
There are sexual services
for women, right?

76
00:03:17,797 --> 00:03:18,965
Huh?

77
00:03:19,032 --> 00:03:23,803
An ordinary housewife stumbles upon
sexual services for women by chance.

78
00:03:24,304 --> 00:03:26,306
But then her daughter finds out by chance.

79
00:03:26,372 --> 00:03:27,907
That's from <i>LN</i>, right?

80
00:03:28,775 --> 00:03:30,677
In the third episode of <i>LN</i>…

81
00:03:32,679 --> 00:03:35,982
I was amazed at how ahead
of the times you were.

82
00:03:36,049 --> 00:03:38,151
-I remember so--
-How about a shared house?

83
00:03:38,218 --> 00:03:41,788
A bookstore owner and an actress
meet by chance

84
00:03:41,854 --> 00:03:43,823
and end up living together by chance.

85
00:03:43,890 --> 00:03:45,725
So come up with those chance scenarios!

86
00:03:45,792 --> 00:03:47,293
As a screenwriter, it's his job!

87
00:03:47,360 --> 00:03:50,296
Wait, an actress and a bookstore owner?

88
00:03:50,363 --> 00:03:52,232
Yup, it's totally from <i>Notting Hill</i>.

89
00:03:52,298 --> 00:03:54,167
Yikes.

90
00:03:54,234 --> 00:03:55,802
Why is he like this?

91
00:03:56,369 --> 00:03:59,639
The truth is,
Mr. Emo announced a hiatus in 2008.

92
00:04:01,107 --> 00:04:04,110
<i>Let's delve into what Emoken
has been up to during his break.</i>

93
00:04:04,177 --> 00:04:06,546
He suddenly developed a passion
for environmental issues,

94
00:04:06,613 --> 00:04:09,949
relocated to Okinawa, and started blogging
about ecology and slow living.

95
00:04:10,016 --> 00:04:13,419
In his personal life, he abruptly married
a model 19 years his junior,

96
00:04:13,486 --> 00:04:14,954
but they split 18 months later.

97
00:04:15,021 --> 00:04:18,358
He raised funds through crowdfunding
to open a salon, but it closed.

98
00:04:18,424 --> 00:04:21,227
Lately, he's been sharing
about his relationship

99
00:04:21,294 --> 00:04:23,296
with an influencer 19 years his junior.

100
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:28,001
Apart from his romantic history,
everything he does is inconsistent.

101
00:04:28,067 --> 00:04:31,437
In fact, the higher-ups are saying
he can't attract enough viewers anymore.

102
00:04:32,505 --> 00:04:35,375
I bet it's tough for him
to admit he's old news now.

103
00:04:36,509 --> 00:04:38,778
Which makes it hard for me
to work with him.

104
00:04:40,480 --> 00:04:41,781
Why don't I tell him?

105
00:04:41,848 --> 00:04:42,682
Huh?

106
00:04:43,249 --> 00:04:44,550
Tell him what?

107
00:04:44,617 --> 00:04:47,820
"Stop sharing old stories.
They're outdated and bothering everyone."

108
00:04:47,887 --> 00:04:49,088
Please don't.

109
00:04:49,155 --> 00:04:51,124
Someone older should tell him.

110
00:04:51,758 --> 00:04:52,892
When's your next meeting?

111
00:04:54,260 --> 00:04:56,329
Wednesday, from 4 p.m.

112
00:04:56,396 --> 00:04:57,930
I happen to be free.

113
00:05:00,533 --> 00:05:01,367
Hey.

114
00:05:01,968 --> 00:05:02,969
Are you okay?

115
00:05:03,036 --> 00:05:04,304
What do you mean?

116
00:05:06,172 --> 00:05:07,173
Nothing.

117
00:05:10,977 --> 00:05:15,915
<i>This man is Mr. Ichiro Ogawa,
EBS TV's counselor.</i>

118
00:05:15,982 --> 00:05:20,486
<i>He was my grandfather
on my late mother's side.</i>

119
00:05:34,600 --> 00:05:35,868
Say, Kiyoshi,

120
00:05:36,436 --> 00:05:38,004
how long are you staying here?

121
00:05:39,105 --> 00:05:41,341
I don't know. I've got to ask Mom.

122
00:05:43,509 --> 00:05:44,377
Am I a bother?

123
00:05:44,444 --> 00:05:45,378
No.

124
00:05:46,713 --> 00:05:48,681
She's a sociologist, right?

125
00:05:52,352 --> 00:05:54,987
<i>Eiji Okuda is about to have an affair
with Ryoko Moriyama.</i>

126
00:05:55,621 --> 00:05:58,124
<i>Ryoko Moriyama
and Tomoko Ogawa are best friends.</i>

127
00:05:59,192 --> 00:06:00,526
<i>It's unsettling.</i>

128
00:06:01,527 --> 00:06:03,996
<i>What's with Eiji Okuda's sexiness?</i>

129
00:06:04,731 --> 00:06:06,999
<i>I didn't get it as a child but now I do.</i>

130
00:06:07,066 --> 00:06:10,603
<i>Anyone would get the butterflies.</i>

131
00:06:11,104 --> 00:06:12,138
<i>And…</i>

132
00:06:12,205 --> 00:06:14,807
<i>I love this person
more than anything in the world.</i>

133
00:06:15,541 --> 00:06:18,911
<i>Eiji Bando's likability just skyrocketed.</i>

134
00:06:18,978 --> 00:06:22,548
<i>A child is happiest
when their parents get along.</i>

135
00:06:23,549 --> 00:06:25,118
<i>And parents are happiest</i>

136
00:06:26,519 --> 00:06:28,287
<i>when children get along.</i>

137
00:06:29,355 --> 00:06:32,525
-This is such a tearjerker.
-<i>So who cares what other people say?</i>

138
00:06:33,893 --> 00:06:37,997
<i>Your dad loves your mom.</i>

139
00:06:38,631 --> 00:06:39,866
<i>A whole lot.</i>

140
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,107
Welcome back.

141
00:06:53,212 --> 00:06:54,046
What?

142
00:06:55,548 --> 00:06:57,884
Junko wants to know
how long we're staying.

143
00:06:58,918 --> 00:07:00,787
As long as <i>Kintsuma</i> is running.

144
00:07:00,853 --> 00:07:02,221
That's a rerun.

145
00:07:03,022 --> 00:07:05,258
Kiyoshi doesn't want to go back.

146
00:07:06,325 --> 00:07:07,627
Dinner isn't ready yet.

147
00:07:09,195 --> 00:07:10,163
What?

148
00:07:11,197 --> 00:07:12,298
Has there been any word?

149
00:07:13,332 --> 00:07:14,434
From your father?

150
00:07:18,471 --> 00:07:19,605
Not today.

151
00:07:20,573 --> 00:07:22,308
Not today? So, not today either.

152
00:07:23,242 --> 00:07:25,144
Is he really in the future?

153
00:07:25,211 --> 00:07:26,279
Maybe he's playing elsewhere.

154
00:07:26,345 --> 00:07:27,680
Hey, be quiet!

155
00:07:28,181 --> 00:07:30,116
<i>Can we read one more? We can?</i>

156
00:07:30,183 --> 00:07:32,819
<i>Okay, the handle is
Mysterious Transfer Student.</i>

157
00:07:32,885 --> 00:07:34,587
-No way.
-That's me!

158
00:07:34,654 --> 00:07:35,788
<i>Hanky-panky apple.</i>

159
00:07:36,289 --> 00:07:39,926
<i>"There's a student in my class
I haven't met yet."</i>

160
00:07:39,992 --> 00:07:42,929
<i>"It seems he hasn't come to school
since I transferred."</i>

161
00:07:42,995 --> 00:07:44,730
<i>"And he won't answer the phone."</i>

162
00:07:45,698 --> 00:07:46,599
<i>"Hey, S."</i>

163
00:07:46,666 --> 00:07:49,402
<i>"If you peek under
your TV's cathode ray tube,</i>

164
00:07:49,469 --> 00:07:52,438
<i>you might be able to see Iyo's pants."</i>

165
00:07:53,606 --> 00:07:55,041
<i>This kid is so silly!</i>

166
00:07:57,977 --> 00:08:00,046
I'm from Class B, Grade 3 at School 6--

167
00:08:00,112 --> 00:08:01,681
The Mysterious Transfer Student.

168
00:08:02,882 --> 00:08:06,352
I'm sorry. He doesn't want to see anyone.

169
00:08:06,919 --> 00:08:10,423
<i>Mysterious Transfer Student,
you've won a present.</i>

170
00:08:10,490 --> 00:08:12,792
<i>Writer Emoken's personal sunglasses.</i>

171
00:08:12,859 --> 00:08:14,961
-Shall we head back?
-<i>You might not want them.</i>

172
00:08:15,528 --> 00:08:17,296
Sunglasses were fine,

173
00:08:17,864 --> 00:08:21,467
but he kept giving away my stuff
like my wristwatch and sneakers.

174
00:08:21,534 --> 00:08:22,735
It was such a pain.

175
00:08:22,802 --> 00:08:26,138
Everyone has interesting pasts, huh?
How about we start discussing--

176
00:08:26,205 --> 00:08:29,575
Zucchi took really good care of me.

177
00:08:29,642 --> 00:08:33,546
Do you guys know
<i>Be Early or There Will Be Hanky-Panky</i>?

178
00:08:33,613 --> 00:08:36,415
It was a program that would never fly
compliance-wise today.

179
00:08:36,482 --> 00:08:40,019
It's not <i>Be Early</i>, it's <i>Go to Bed Early
or There Will Be Hanky-Panky</i>.

180
00:08:40,086 --> 00:08:40,920
Who?

181
00:08:41,621 --> 00:08:43,589
Someone gets what I'm talking about.

182
00:08:43,656 --> 00:08:46,025
This is our company's counselor,
Mr. Ogawa.

183
00:08:46,526 --> 00:08:48,528
I've been to a public filming
of <i>Hanky-Panky.</i>

184
00:08:49,595 --> 00:08:52,965
Have you heard of the drama
featuring the Hanky-Panky girls?

185
00:08:53,032 --> 00:08:55,701
<i>Hanky-Panky on Friday,
and More Hanky-Panky on Saturday</i>.

186
00:08:55,768 --> 00:08:58,237
No way, that's my debut piece!

187
00:08:58,304 --> 00:09:00,273
Wow. It's not even on Wikipedia.

188
00:09:00,339 --> 00:09:01,574
What are you, a Showa geek?

189
00:09:02,208 --> 00:09:04,911
You can ask me anything up until Showa 61.

190
00:09:04,977 --> 00:09:07,313
I'll take it from here.
Everyone, back to your jobs.

191
00:09:07,380 --> 00:09:08,514
Or head home if you can.

192
00:09:09,348 --> 00:09:10,349
Good work.

193
00:09:12,985 --> 00:09:16,222
Let me tell you,
that drama was such a pain to make.

194
00:09:16,289 --> 00:09:19,025
The other lead was such a poor actor
we had to pull in--

195
00:09:19,091 --> 00:09:20,359
Toshinori Omi.

196
00:09:20,426 --> 00:09:23,195
Exactly, Omi accepted the role.

197
00:09:23,262 --> 00:09:25,064
-And the theme song was…
-Senri Oe.

198
00:09:25,131 --> 00:09:26,866
Senri Oe, exactly!

199
00:09:26,933 --> 00:09:28,467
No, it was Omega Tribe.

200
00:09:28,534 --> 00:09:30,803
Wait, you know more than I do.

201
00:09:30,870 --> 00:09:32,305
Let's grab drinks in Kasumicho.

202
00:09:33,839 --> 00:09:36,442
You were late.
How many bars did you hit up?

203
00:09:36,509 --> 00:09:37,410
